Practical Alchemy is the study and/or practice some modern chemists do of ancient alchemy.  Someone who says they practice practicle alchemy usually are doing either of two things:

# Studying ancient alchemy and explaining it in terms of current chemistry, and whether this principle (learned from studying) is related to why some alchemic experiments turned out.
# Someone who practices working experiments, usually from websites like http://www.levity.com/alchemy/physical.html which have some purpose, though arcane.